<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-407-926  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 407 926.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The LocalNetter  Nov 1990 v10 n11 p213(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Allied Telesis unveils new LAN fanout units. (CentreCOM 280,CentreCOM 480) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Allied Telesis Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Allied Telesis CentreCOM 280 (Computer communications equipment)(Product introduction)Allied Telesis CentreCOM 480 (Computer communications equipment)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCommunications Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Allied Telesis Unveils New LAN Fanout Units Allied Telesis, Inc., announcedthe introduction of two Ethernet LAN expansion products, the CentreCOM 280and 480, dual- and four-port fanout units.andM;Normally, a single drop cable connects users to the backbone via a singletransceiver.andP;  The CentreCOM 280 and 480 also connect to transceivers likeindividuals nodes, but with the added capability of connecting two or fouradditional users or nodes.andM;The CentreCOM 280/480 fanouts comply with the IEEE 802.3 AUI (Attachment UnitInterface) specifications.andP;  Diagnostic LED indicators monitor Transmission,Receive, and Collision activities.andP;  No outside power source is required(power is drawn from the DTEs connected to the fanouts).andP;  Optional mountingbrackets are available for ceiling or wall installation.andM;Both new products are available immediately through ATI distributors andresellers.andP;  Introductory single-unit prices will be in effect until the endof the year.andP;  The dual-port unit is $245, while the four-port unit is $375.andO;A two-year warranty covers both products.andM;Information: Allied Telesis Inc., (415) 964-2771, Fax (415) 964-0944.andO;</TEXT></DOC>